data.content:
Here's the output — PascalCase as expected:

```json
{
  "Name": "Alice",
  "Age": 30
}
```

The key is `JsonNamingPolicy.PascalCase`, which was added as a built-in policy in .NET 9. It converts the record's lowercase constructor parameter names (`name`, `age`) to PascalCase (`Name`, `Age`) automatically — no custom naming policy needed.

The full program is at `PersonApp/Program.cs`:

```csharp
using System.Text.Json;

var options = new JsonSerializerOptions
{
    PropertyNamingPolicy = JsonNamingPolicy.PascalCase,
    WriteIndented = true
};

var person = new Person("Alice", 30);
string json = JsonSerializer.Serialize(person, options);
Console.WriteLine(json);

public record Person(string name, int age);
```
